# Normalize all text files to LF in the repo, on every platform.
#
# Why this matters here: the generator's hand-rolled YAML parser
# (generator/serialize.mjs) strips a trailing comment with /\s+#.*$/, a regex
# that does NOT match when the line ends in CRLF — `.` won't cross the \r and
# `$` won't sit before it. On a Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true, that
# left `taxonomy: default-v1  # ...` parsed WITH the comment glued on, breaking
# build.mjs and the determinism/harvest tests. Forcing LF keeps the parser (and
# byte-for-byte determinism of data/tree.json) stable regardless of the cloner's
# git config. See tree.config.yml's header note about the fragile parser.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never touch line endings.
*.jpg  binary
*.JPG  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.png  binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary
